‹g¬]<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1316";s:4:"name";s:19:"Parkinson's Disease";s:4:"slug";s:18:"parkinsons-disease";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1316";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4182:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Parkinson‚Äôs disease has a strong connection with Hollywood in the sense that many good movies have been made on this subject. Another connection is that with actor Michael J Fox who has since </span><span style="font-weight: 400;">become ‚Äúone of the best-known individuals alive with Parkinson‚Äôs disease.‚Äù</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">PD is a progressive nervous system disorder that severely affects movement of an individual. Noticeable symptoms start to appear gradually, leading to almost impairment of an individual completely. A lot of movies have shown us a glimpse of the progression of the disease. Slurry speech, restricted or difficulty in moving with little or no expression in the face could be a sign of Parkinson‚Äôs disease. There is no cure for the ailment and medicines do improve the symptoms of the patients.</span>

<b>Symptoms</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Symptoms of the disease may progress at a different pace for an individual and these symptoms may show gradually:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Tremor- Hand tremors are the most common, to begin with. These could get severe as the disease progresses.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Slowed movement- You will notice a slight dip in your pace while performing different day-to-day activities like walking or getting up.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Rigid muscles.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sleep disorders or problems in falling asleep.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Impaired posture.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Imbalance.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Slurred speech.</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Change in handwriting leading to almost incomprehensible writing.</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Causes</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">A lot of research has gone into understanding the cause of this ailment. PD and its aftereffects are appalling as it interferes with the daily living of people. Here are some of the known causes of the disease:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Genes: Genes could play a very important role in dissemination of this ailment.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Exposure to toxins: Exposure to pesticides and herbicides could trigger the illness.</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;"> ¬†</span><span style="font-weight: 400;">Sex: Men are more likely to be affected by the disease than women.</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Treatments</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">There is no chance that the ailment is fully cured or treated. However, antibiotic medications are available to manage the symptoms and relieve you of the trauma of the disease itself. You could also be advised a surgery for treating the illness. Aerobic exercises, physical therapy and language-speech therapy is also given.</span>

<b>Going beyond in the holistic approach</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Louise Hay, motivational leader and empowerment coach who has done path breaking work in supporting HIV/AIDS patients and their families, has said that, ‚ÄúIllness however mild or severe is an indicator of your emotional state, caused by your thoughts and focus.‚Äù </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">According to her, the main cause of Parkinson‚Äôs disease is: </span><b>Fear and intense desire to control everything and everyone.</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">One way of healing this is through saying or writing affirmations. Doing this regularly can help to reduce the debilitating effects of this illness. </span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Her affirmation for treating the ailment is</span><b>: I relax knowing that I am safe. Life is for me, and I trust the process of life.</b>";s:6:"parent";s:1:"0";s:5:"count";s:1:"0";}}